column25: Some kind of psychotherapy must be incorporated in the programme of every trainee with respect of her/his  preferences.
"The doctor as a drug"- each psychiatrist must have some psychotherapeutic abilities to be usefull for the patient and for him/herself.

column32: Cognitive-behavioural therapy, Art therapy, Positive psychotherapy, PSYCHODRAMA METHOD /we are best at this method in our institution, especially MONODRAMA, we have one of the best clinical psychologists trained particularly with great emphasis in this technique; we have developed our original theory and practice of applying PSYCHODRAMA in the psychotherapy of schizophrenic patients./] group psychotherapy, emphatic psychotherapy /also one of our original inventions/, you cannot imagine the astonishing results accomplished with this unconventional altruistic technique among all kinds of psychiatric patients ranging from anxiety and affective disorders through substance addictions and psychotic disorders, especially for florid mania syndromes.

column25: I'd like to have at least enough education/training during my residence in psychiatry to obtain general knowledge of the different psychitherapeutic modalities and how they can help. Not every psychiatrist needs to be a psychotherapist, but at least every psychiatrist needs to have very good knowledge about the possibilities psychotherapy offers. All modalities should be introduced to psychiatric trainees so that everyone can decide which one they like.
I think that would be useful, even necessary, no matter if person will practise it.

Psychoterapeutic skills are important part of understanding the phenomenology of normality and abnormality in psychology and clinical psychiatry.Without this ability psychiatry is like every other medical specialty.It gives comfort ot knowing your patients,and knowing yourself in different clinical situations.
I think it is useful psychotherapy to be included in the speciality of psychiatry or at least to be optional.
column69: I think it has to be included in the speciality of psychiatry and funded by the hospital where we work, because for now the situation in my country is that we have to pay for psychotherapy on our own and it is very expensive compared to our income.

column25: I need supervision in counselling and interviewing patients as part of my professional work of psychiatrist and I need also personal psychotherapy
column32: Psychodynamic Psychotherapy, Counselling, Family and Systematic Therapy, not sure of any others
Family and Marital Therapy, Group Psychotherapy

column16: Group Psychotherapy - Psychodrama, Cognitive Behavioral psychotherapy
